                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16269387" author="rohini" created="Tue, 28 Nov 2017 20:08:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While checking code to ensure that we have not missed any other place, found a couple of cases.&lt;br/&gt;
1) We should also call ScriptState.setFileName in the PigServer.registerScript(String fileName, Map&amp;lt;String,String&amp;gt; params,List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt; paramsFiles) &lt;br/&gt;
2) org.apache.pig.pigunit.pig.PigServer also requires the change&lt;br/&gt;
3) GruntParser.loadScript is another place ScriptState.setFileName and  ScriptState.setScript is required. run/exec commands go through this code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16277184" author="satishsaley" created="Mon, 4 Dec 2017 18:18:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16277222" author="rohini" created="Mon, 4 Dec 2017 18:38:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1) FileLocalizer.fetchFile will be repeated twice which will be wasteful if the file is being fetched from hdfs/s3. Can you create a overloaded loadScript method that takes FetchFile as well?&lt;br/&gt;
2) beginNestedScript can be changed to beginNestedScript(File) and the setters can be called in that method instead of doing it in loadScript.&lt;br/&gt;
3) Initializing serializedScript and truncatedScript to &quot;&quot; is redundant.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16277356" author="satishsaley" created="Mon, 4 Dec 2017 19:40:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16277442" author="rohini" created="Mon, 4 Dec 2017 20:28:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Committed to trunk. Thanks for fixing this Satish.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
